<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="87" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d87">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.0141 Phoenix Group/7</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lindsay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 223</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-16">July 16, 1937</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honour to inform you that
                                the attention of His Majesty’s Government in the United Kingdom has
                                been drawn to the recent visit to Canton Island of the United States
                                minesweeper <hi rend="italic">Avocet</hi>, of which no prior
                                official communication was made. I have accordingly been instructed
                                to transmit to you herewith, for the information of the United
                                States Government, the enclosed copy of an Order in Council of the
                                13th [<hi rend="italic">18th</hi>] March, 1937,<note n="28" xml:id="d87fn28">Not printed.</note> by which Canton Island and
                                the other islands in the Phoenix Group were incorporated in the
                                Gilbert and Ellice Islands Colony.</p>
                            <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed>R. C. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lindsay</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>